UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Don\'t go thinking that was too easy. Far greater dangers lurk deeper in the woods. ',RequestItemsText='You still hunting wolves?',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=0 WHERE id=26618;##Wolves At Our Heels
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Ah yes, a nice lump you have there!  Let me just get this seasoned with my secret spices (no looking!) and get them to skittering on a skillet for a while...\n
And, although Dusky Crab Cakes are my specialty and I won\'t give out the recipe, here\'s the recipe for a dish that\'s almost as good. ',RequestItemsText='Hail, $N. Did you get that lump meat for me?',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=0 WHERE id=26623;## Dusky Crab Cakes
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Mmm-mmm! The skirtsteak\'s the best part. It\'s not an efficient way to cook, though.\n
Here, have this recipe. It\'s a little different, but flank meat\'s easier to come by when you really need a meal. ',RequestItemsText='Were you able to find five wolf skirt steaks yet?',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=0 WHERE id=26620;##Seasoned Wolf Kabobs
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Impressive, $N. It would seem that you are capable enough to handle yourself. Perhaps a more suitable challenge could be found for one of your abilities.',RequestItemsText='$N, how fares the hunt?',NextQuestId=26689,PrevQuestId=0 WHERE id=26688; ##Worgen in the Woods
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='You performed well against the Shadow Weavers, $N. But even now, years after their first arrival, there seem to be so many to replace the ones we kill.\n
I will put my faith in Master Carevin. No doubt he will get to the bottom of the problem.',RequestItemsText='Back so sooon, $N? I hope you haven\'t come to tell me you\'ve given up?',NextQuestId=26690,PrevQuestId=26688 WHERE id=26689;## The Rotting Orchard
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='I\'ve been told there\'s signs of activity at Begga\'s Haunt. People have reported seeing lights in the tower to the east of town.\n
Few would be bold enough to stay that close to Deadwind Pass. You\'re the first to report since I\'ve learned about this; go check it out and make sure whatever\'s in there is human. ',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=26653,PrevQuestId=26618 WHERE id=26627;## The Hermit
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Splendid, $N. For your service to the people of Darkshire you shall be rewarded. ',RequestItemsText='I don\'t have authority to order you around, $N. But at least think of the citizens here who''ll be suffering if those undead are allowed to lurk.',NextQuestId=26686,PrevQuestId=26618 WHERE id=26645;## The Night Watch
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Can I help you?',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=26667,PrevQuestId=0 WHERE id=26666;## The Legend of Stalvan
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Why yes, I used to own a looking glass.',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=26684,PrevQuestId=0 WHERE id=26683;## Look To The Stars
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Ah, ghost hair thread is what you need, is it?  I\'m afraid I have none in stock, but I can make some for you...if you can supply the ghost hair.',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=26652,PrevQuestId=26627 WHERE id=26653;## Supplies from Darkshire
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='What is this?  A comb?  It\'s lovely!  And it glides through my hair as if it weren\'t the stiff, stringy horror that it is.\b
Oh, if only I had a mirror... ',RequestItemsText='<Sob> Oh please, don\'t look at me!  I tore out these eyes with my own hands, but I can still feel your gaze!\n
I\'m hideous!  Hideous!  Please, look away!! ',NextQuestId=26654,PrevQuestId=26653 WHERE id=26652;## Ghost Hair Thread
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='By the light... you actually went and got it?\n
I\'m shocked. I suppose I owe you thanks for returning it to the archives.',RequestItemsText='Look, sir, I really don\'t want any trouble... ',NextQuestId=26669,PrevQuestId=26666 WHERE id=26667;##The Stolen Letters
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Most superb!  This will work perfectly.  Many thanks!',RequestItemsText='I showed Cog the beginnings of our star-viewing machine.  He was impressed.  Did you happen to find a reflective device?',NextQuestId=26685,PrevQuestId=26683 WHERE id=26684;## The Insane Ghoul
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='I can make a spool of ghost hair thread with this, and have a few strands to spare.  Here are some coins for those extra strands.',RequestItemsText='I sens that you have seen Blind Mary. You have my comb...?',NextQuestId=26655,PrevQuestId=26652 WHERE id=26654;##Return the Comb
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='$N, to be honest with you, I did not believe that you would get this far, but you are clearly a $C to be reckoned with. In fact, if you wish to formally join Master Carevin\'s struggle, I will gladly write for you a letter of recommendation.',RequestItemsText='Intimidating beasts aren\'t they? But have no fear, $N, those who stand for the Light will never fail!',NextQuestId=26691,PrevQuestId=26689 WHERE id=26690;##Vile and Tained
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='The people of Darkshire thank you, $N.  You have proven yourself to be a great ally of The Night Watch. ',RequestItemsText='I hope you\'re not going back on your word. $N.',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=26645 WHERE id=26686;##Bones That Walk
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Delightful!  This will do splendidly...\n
Here, good $N, take this as payment for your honorable deed. ',RequestItemsText='I need to string the ghost hair thread along my door and my windows to keep out unwanted spirits.  Did you get it for me?',NextQuestId=26660,PrevQuestId=26654 WHERE id=26655;##Deliver the Thread
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='At last!  The stargazing device is complete!  Thank you, $N.  Now I can continue my research. . . ',RequestItemsText='Were you able to convince Zzarc\'Vul to lend us his monocle for our experiment? ',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=26684 WHERE id=26685;##Classy Glass
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='You need some Zombie Juice, do you?  Hmm...that\'s some strong stuff - I don\'t usually get requests for it. ',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=26661,PrevQuestId=26655 WHERE id=26660;## Zombie Juice
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Good,  you got the rot blossoms.\n
I\'ll whip up the zombie juice... it\'s strong stuff, I warn you.',RequestItemsText='Hi, $N. Do you have those rot blossoms for me yet?',NextQuestId=26676,PrevQuestId=26660 WHERE id=26661;##Gather Rot Blossoms
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='This was all you found?\n
That\'s bad news, I\'m afraid... ',RequestItemsText='You\'re back in one piece, I see.',NextQuestId=26670,PrevQuestId=26667 WHERE id=26669;##In A Dark Corner
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Excuse me for my cold reception, $N, but as I\'m sure you can tell, I am an extremely busy man. I see that you have impressed Calor--and I assure you, that is no small feat--and that he has given his recommendation.\n
There are unsavory types afoot, $N, and we can use the help of all who have proven themselves. We battle against demons, the undead, and those who would provide them aid. Be vigilant, be wary, and trust none who would not give aid to our cause.\n
Glory under the Light. ',RequestItemsText='Yes, what is it? Make it quick, I\'ve pressing matters to attend to.',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=26690 WHERE id=26691;##Worgen In The Woods
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='A thousand thanks, $N.  You warm an old man\'s heart with your foolish-...I mean...with your kindness!\n
Here you are, friend.  Take this as a token of my gratitude. ',RequestItemsText='I need that Zombie Juice to keep me warm on these cold, dark nights.  Did you get it for me? ',NextQuestId=26680,PrevQuestId=26661 WHERE id=26676;##Juice Delivery
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='You actually went and got it?!\n
I don\'t know whether to call you brave or insane. But once again, my archives thank you. ',RequestItemsText='I told you, $N, it\'s not worth pursuing. . .',NextQuestId=26671,PrevQuestId=26669 WHERE id=26670;## Roland's Doom
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Thank the Nec-...well, thank YOU, $N!  You have more than earned your reward.\n
Aha!  Happy!  Happy nights ahead!!',RequestItemsText='Do you have my crate? If so, then please... give it to me quickly!',NextQuestId=26677,PrevQuestId=26676 WHERE id=26680;##Ogre Thieves
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='I can\'t thank you enough... I had hoped for this to be a joyous reunion, but the more I learn, the less glad I am to have asked.\n
But I must know. ',RequestItemsText='You\'re back! Did you find anything about my brother?',NextQuestId=26672,PrevQuestId=26670 WHERE id=26671;## The Fate of Stalvan Mistmantle
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='How interesting. It\'s been quite a while since I\'ve seen such a ring... ',RequestItemsText='What dark whispers guide you to my door, $C? ',NextQuestId=26674,PrevQuestId=26671 WHERE id=26672;##Clawing at the Truth
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Master Harris may have been right. I would have been better to leave the past behind.\n
I\'ve got a new life now. Whether it\'s that of a monster or a man is up to me.\n
As for you, I cannot thank you enough for your assistance, regardless of the outcome. Please, take this with my thanks.',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=26785,PrevQuestId=26672 WHERE id=26674;##Mistmantle's Revenge
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Tobias is staying in town still?\n
Master Harris warned him not to pursue his brother\'s fate. We all lead new lives now, after all. But the past is hard to let go of... ',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=26717,PrevQuestId=26674 WHERE id=26785;#Part of the Pack
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Ah, thanks.  These will do just the trick! ',RequestItemsText='I\'m sure you could find plenty of ribs in Raven Hill as well, but you might not want to wander so far at night... ',NextQuestId=26681,PrevQuestId=26680 WHERE id=26677;#Ghoulish Effigy
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='<Ello looks at the letter, and immediately pales.>\n
You fool! You\'ve doomed us all! ',RequestItemsText='A letter? What\'s this all about? ',NextQuestId=26727,PrevQuestId=26677 WHERE id=26681;#Note to the Mayor
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Thank the light, he\'s gone...\n
I\'ll say you\'ve made amends by helping save the lives of those here, $N. ',RequestItemsText='Don\'t just stand there! He\'s right outside! By the light, man, do something!',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=26681 WHERE id=26727;#The Embalmer's Revenge
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='I saw you drop a few of them from here. Nice work.\n
Here\'s your reward, on behalf of the Night Watch. ',RequestItemsText='If you\'d rather just sit around camp and have a drink of two, that\'s fine too, I guess.',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=0 WHERE id=25235;# Vulgar Vul'Gol
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='I thank you, $C... and I\'m sure the worgen that may be returned to sanity with the potion this will make would thank you too. ',RequestItemsText='Do you have the corpseweed? ',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=0 WHERE id=26707;#A Deadly Vine
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='',RequestItemsText='Did you go look yet?',NextQuestId=26719,PrevQuestId=26785 WHERE id=26717;#The Yorgen Worgen
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Welcome to our humble camp. I wouldn\'t call it pleasant, but it\'s at least somewhat private.\n
Beg your pardon? A worgen at the farm? ',RequestItemsText='What brings you out this way, my good sir? ',NextQuestId=26720,PrevQuestId=26717 WHERE id=26719;#Delivery to Master Harris
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='You have brought peace to those who knew only misery, $N. Be proud.',RequestItemsText='The spirits deserve rest.',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=0 WHERE id=26777;#Soothing Spirits
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Oh thank you, thank you! You\'ve saved me from having to go out in the woods with those awful things!\n
At least for a day, that is... ',RequestItemsText='Did you get it? Please tell me you got it... ',NextQuestId=26787,PrevQuestId=0 WHERE id=26721;#The Jitters-Bugs
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='You\'ve got him!\n
No time to lose, then. We\'ll prepare to administer the serum right away.\n
JITTERS! Get ready! ',RequestItemsText='Have you searched the Addle Stead thoroughly?\n I\'d check the very back of barn. I\'d check the very back of the barn. Many things can lurk in such a building',NextQuestId=26760,PrevQuestId=26719 WHERE id=26720;#A Curse We Cannot Lift
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Success... Finally! I can\'t thank you enough for giving me the chance to work the cure myself.\n
Our new friend may be in need of some help as well. You might want to speak with him. ',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=26720 WHERE id=26760;#Cry for the Moon
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='His clothes and bloodstains? If it\'s not tricks, it\'s something worse... ',RequestItemsText='What did you find?',NextQuestId=26724,PrevQuestId=26760 WHERE id=26723;#The Fate of Morbent Fel
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='The cries grow softer for now. Light bless you, $N>. ',RequestItemsText='I can still hear them...',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=26760 WHERE id=26778;#The Cries of the Dead
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Thank you! Oh, thank you. I never thought I\'d be happy to smell those brains, but I am now that I didn\'t have to get them!\n
Here\'s your reward as promised... ',RequestItemsText='Did you get them? Did you?',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=26721 WHERE id=26787;#Bear in Mind
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Morgan Ladimore?\n
Ahh, yes, of course. His was a long and sorrowful tale. I knew him, well, before he left for the war, but that was the last time I saw him. A noble and good man, he was, but he suffered a bad end.\n
Here, I should have something here that can tell the tale better than my own recollections... ',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=26794,PrevQuestId=0 WHERE id=26793;#The Weathered Grave
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='It\'s heartening to see one so recently recovered be so concerned with the plight of others. Sven spares himself suffering by not dwelling on his own misfortune. ',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=26725,PrevQuestId=26723 WHERE id=26724;#The Lurking Lich
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='<Buried in the cold dirt, you find a brilliant metal shaft. But there are holes where pieces of the artifact are clearly missing.> ',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=26753,PrevQuestId=26724 WHERE id=26725;#Guided by the light
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='<In the dirt of this alcove, your eye catches the shine of brilliant metal. You\'ve found another piece of the artifact!> ',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=26722,PrevQuestId=26725 WHERE id=26753;#The Halls of the Dead
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='<In the darkest depths of this earthen tunnel, you spy the faintest gleam. The last piece is found!> ',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=26754,PrevQuestId=26753 WHERE id=26722;#Buried Below
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='May the disgusting monster stay dead this time!\n
I\'ll head down there and scatter his remains to ash myself, $N. You\'ve done a great thing; perhaps in time Duskwood can return to its former peaceful state. ',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=26722 WHERE id=26754;#Morbent's Bane
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Morgan Ladimore? Never heard of...\n
Oh, you mean Mor\'Ladim! I guess you haven\'t heard the story?\n
Well, I\'ll give you the short version. A powerful undead calling itself Mor\'Ladim has been wandering Duskwood. From what we\'ve gathered, it appears to be the undead body of Morgan Ladimore, of whom you apparently know. He\'s been causing us all sorts of problems, attacking Watchmen on patrol and killing people.\n
<She sizes you up.>\n
You seem to be capable enough, maybe you could lay him to rest. ',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=26795,PrevQuestId=26793 WHERE id=26794;#Morgan Ladimore
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='You killed him? That\'s no small accomplishment, $N! On behalf of the people of Darkshire and the Night Watch, I thank you.\n
Ah... there is one small matter, however... ',RequestItemsText='I don\'t blame you if you\'re having trouble with him, $N. Some of our strongest Watchers have been lost to Mor\'Ladim. ',NextQuestId=26796,PrevQuestId=26794 WHERE id=26795;#Mor'Ladim
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='Yes? My father...\n
<Her eyes become downcast.>\n
I wish... there was something I could have done for him... If only I had talked to him before he... ',RequestItemsText='',NextQuestId=26797,PrevQuestId=26795 WHERE id=26796;#The Daughter Who Lived
UPDATE quest_template SET OfferRewardText='<A ghostly voice sounds on the wind...>\n
This is...? Sarah? Could it be she\'s still alive? The weight is removed from my shoulders...\n
$N. Take my sword, Archeus. As my soul is put to rest, I have no more need for it. It was forged to do good, and though I have proved myself unworthy to hold it, perhaps you will carry on the Light through it.\n
Lys, my love... ',RequestItemsText='Leave me be... ',NextQuestId=0,PrevQuestId=26796 WHERE id=26797;#A Daughter's Love


